    question: "What's the difference between cash back and points?",
    answer: "<strong>Cash back</strong> has a fixed value (1% = 1¢ per dollar). <strong>Points</strong> can vary in value (typically 1-2¢ each) depending on how you redeem them. Some 'cash back' cards like Chase Freedom actually earn points that can be transferred to travel partners for higher value when combined with cards like Sapphire Preferred."
